{
  "meta": {
    "id": "parallel-refund-approval",
    "name": "Parallel Refund Approval",
    "description": "Forks a refund request into an LLM eligibility analysis and an approval-gated refund agent. The agent pauses for tool approval inside the parallel branch; after approve/reject, join merges both results and the triage composer drafts the customer-facing reply.",
    "complexity": "advanced",
    "category": "support",
    "tags": ["parallel", "fork", "join", "tool-approval", "refund", "hitl"],
    "agents": ["refund-actions-agent", "support-triage-composer"]
  },
  "graph": {
    "version": 1,
    "nodes": [
      {
        "id": "start_1",
        "type": "start",
        "position": { "x": 40, "y": 280 },
        "data": {}
      },
      {
        "id": "set_ticket",
        "type": "set_state",
        "position": { "x": 200, "y": 280 },
        "data": {
          "key": "ticket",
          "from_key": "input"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "fork_1",
        "type": "fork",
        "position": { "x": 400, "y": 280 },
        "data": {
          "join": "join_1"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "llm_eligibility",
        "type": "llm",
        "position": { "x": 640, "y": 120 },
        "data": {
          "provider": "openai",
          "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
          "checkpoint": true,
          "prompt": "You are a refund eligibility analyst. Assess ONLY whether the following support ticket looks eligible for a refund and note any risk factors.\n\nReturn at most 6 lines covering:\n- Eligibility: eligible | needs_review | not_eligible\n- Risk level: low | medium | high\n- Key policy signals (defective product, duplicate charge, within return window, etc.)\n- One-line recommendation for the refund operator\n\nDo not invent missing facts. Do not process the refund.\n\nTicket:\n{{ticket}}",
          "output_key": "eligibility_analysis"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "agent_refund",
        "type": "agent",
        "position": { "x": 640, "y": 400 },
        "data": {
          "agent_ref": "refund-actions-agent",
          "require_tool_approval": true,
          "checkpoint": true,
          "message": "Process this refund request. Extract order_id, amount, and reason from the ticket and call issue_refund.\n\nTicket:\n{{ticket}}",
          "output_key": "refund_result"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "join_1",
        "type": "join",
        "position": { "x": 900, "y": 280 },
        "data": {
          "output_key": "analyses"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "agent_compose",
        "type": "agent",
        "position": { "x": 1100, "y": 280 },
        "data": {
          "agent_ref": "support-triage-composer",
          "checkpoint": true,
          "message": "Support ticket:\n{{ticket}}\n\n--- Analysis 1: refund eligibility ---\n{{eligibility_analysis}}\n\n--- Analysis 2: refund action result ---\n{{refund_result}}\n\nProduce the triage summary and the suggested reply. Treat the refund action result as the source of truth for whether a refund was issued or rejected.",
          "output_key": "triage_summary"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "stop_1",
        "type": "stop",
        "position": { "x": 1320, "y": 280 },
        "data": {}
      }
    ],
